    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>SPAWNS ONLY AT NIGHT =(</font>, By Solax kamikaze</b><br><br> <p>&nbsp;For all of you people who saw Pyzjn in the day, the reason is because no one had attacked her when she spawned at night.  When you did finally see her, it was day time and so you probably thought 'oh, she does spawn in the day!'  But really this is not true.</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>TRIGGERS</font>, By Lethina</b><br><br>
<p>I have spent enough time camping the ruins to tell you all that she can spawn at any time of the day/night.  The skeletons at the ruins have nothing to do with her spawning [you killing them just helps pass the time and makes it easier to detect her pet with sense undead].  I have also discovered that her placeholder is &#34;mangy rat&#34; ... not &#34;a mangy rat&#34;.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
 Tovax and Varsoon have NOTHING to do with it.  Kill every mangy rat you see [just to be safe] and she WILL spawn.  I think she spawns just slightly down the hill toward BB ... i.e. the same roaming path as the mangy rat ... rather than just spawning directly in the ruins.  She DOES go to the ruins and stay there though.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
 Hope this helps.  If anyone disproves any of these theories, please post here so I know =)<br>
<br>
=============<br>
Scott Simmons<br>
Web Commerce Developer<br>
EC Outlook<br>
614.526.3689<br>
www.ecoutlook.com<br>
=============</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>GLOWING BLACK STONE</font>, By Karyon</b><br><br> Remembering that it is a GAME.  The price of anything is what someone values it at.  I have got the GBS 5 times.  Traded 3 for some nice items, given two away to close friends.  They in turn traded them and got some very nice items.<P>
 So hang in there,keep trying.  She will drop it when she is triggered to.  Oh and Varsoon, and the other necro don't have anything to do with her.  <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>THIS IS TOO FUNNY</font>, By Anonymous</b><br><br>I was medding near the ruins in Qeynos hills on my way to blackburrow on an errand.  A skeleton attacked me and so I killed it.  There was another player there who accused me of camp stealing, so I moved away the ruins and sat down again, to the southwest I think.  Along came Pyjn or whatever her name is, and since a few necros have killed me in the past,I decided to take revenge.  It took one nuke at lvl 39, and I looted this stone off her body--nice item.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>A FEW THOUGHTS...</font>, By Borialis sorrowthorn </b><br><br>I have camped and gotten a GBS.  A few problems with the other posts, I camped her for around 50 hours on and off before I ended up getting it, yes I was very lucky.  First of all, she does NOT only spawn at night.  I have seen her spawn during the day.  Second of all, and this can't be proved, but I do belive tovax and varsoon have something to do with the spawn.  I have seen Varsoon spawn right in the middle of the ruins, then upon killing him, I heard someone yell that they killed varsoon, and then I found pyzjn and killed her.  She didn't have the stone that time, but still, that seems kinda connected to me.<P>
One advantage I had being a necro, is to use sense undead, keep using it and kill everything that comes up. Pyzjn's pet comes up on it.  So as long as you keep sensing, and kill all the undead in Qeynos Hills, you should be fine.  I ended up logging online and seeing her right in front of me one day, that's the time she dropped it, not all the hours I camped her.  Just a little FYI, I hope this has helped.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
